 1 | # Codebase Brain 🧠
 2 | 
 3 | ![Tests](https://img.shields.io/badge/tests-passing-brightgreen)
 4 | ![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-blue)
 5 | ![Built with IBM Bob](https://img.shields.io/badge/built%20with-IBM%20Bob-blue)
 6 | 
 7 | > Stop explaining your codebase from scratch every single AI session.
 8 | 
 9 | ## The Problem
10 | 
11 | Every developer knows this pain. You spend 30 messages 
12 | explaining your codebase to an AI, get a partial answer, 
13 | then start a new session and explain everything again. 
14 | Forever. On a simple project this is annoying. On a 
15 | complex multi-system codebase — it costs weeks.
16 | 
17 | ## The Solution
18 | 
19 | Codebase Brain uses IBM Bob to generate three permanent 
20 | artifacts that give any complex codebase instant memory:
21 | 
22 | | Artifact | What It Does | Size |
23 | |---|---|---|
24 | | AGENTS.md | Complete technical brain — architecture, failures, gotchas | 300+ lines |
25 | | Slash Commands | Domain expert commands any developer can invoke | 2,333 lines |
26 | | Domain Skill | Makes Bob a senior engineer on your codebase instantly | 545 lines |
27 | 
28 | ## Results
29 | 
30 | | Before | After |
31 | |---|---|
32 | | 30 messages to establish context | 1 command |
33 | | Start from zero every session | Permanent memory |
34 | | Only you understand the codebase | Any developer contributes instantly |
35 | | Weeks to onboard a new developer | 60 seconds |
36 | 
37 | ## How It Works
38 | 
39 | **Step 1** — Point IBM Bob at your repository
40 | 
41 | **Step 2** — Bob reads every file and generates AGENTS.md 
42 | with complete architecture, signal chains, failure modes, 
43 | and gotchas
44 | 
45 | **Step 3** — Bob creates slash commands encoding deep 
46 | domain expertise for your specific codebase
47 | 
48 | **Step 4** — Bob generates a domain expert skill that 
49 | makes any future Bob session an instant expert
50 | 
51 | **Step 5** — Any developer or future Bob session has 
52 | full context in 60 seconds
53 | 
54 | ## Demo
55 | 
56 | Built on a real-world humanoid robotics codebase 
57 | (ArduPilot SITL + Gazebo Harmonic). Bob generated:
58 | 
59 | - Complete signal chain: MAVLink → ArduPilot → 
60 |   Plugin → Gazebo joints
61 | - 10 critical gotchas identified
62 | - 10 failure modes with root causes and fixes
63 | - All 30+ files documented with breaking change warnings
64 | 
65 | ## Bob Sessions
